%20like%20a%20star%20before%20I%20become%20one%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20husband%20tells%20his%20pregnant%20wife%20and%20two%20sons.%20Years%20later%2C%20the%20eldest%20son%20Kevin%20(Zac%20Efron)%20can%20be%20seen%20squirming%20on%20a%20concrete%20floor%2C%20trying%20to%20get%20back%20on%20his%20feet%20with%20seconds%20left%20on%20the%20clock%20while%20battling%20the%20most%20excruciating%20pain.%20Kerry%20(Jeremy%20Allen%20White)%20exhibits%20extreme%20masochistic%20tendencies%2C%20as%20he%20forces%20himself%20to%20run%20with%20his%20new%20prosthetic%20leg%2C%20wincing%20in%20pain%20every%20few%20steps.%20And%20in%20one%20of%20the%20most%20chilling%20scenes%20in%20the%20film%2C%20when%20Kevin%20finds%20David%20(Harris%20Dickinson)%20vomiting%20blood%20in%20a%20bathroom%20stall%2C%20he%20quips%20they%20should%20cancel%20his%20trip%20to%20Japan.%20Seconds%20later%2C%20both%20Kevin%20and%20David%20burst%20out%20laughing%2C%20fully%20aware%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20an%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20facade%20of%20being%20able%20to%20endure%20inhuman%20pain%20is%20something%20that%E2%80%99s%20ingrained%20into%20Von%20Erichs%20from%20an%20early%20age.%20A%20middle-class%2C%20suburban%20family%20living%20in%20Texas%2C%20striving%20for%20the%20American%20dream%2C%20Kevin%20keeps%20hearing%20how%20his%20family%20name%20is%20cursed.%20His%20parents%20lost%20their%20first-born%2C%20Jack%20Jr%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%20five.%20However%2C%20the%20patriarch%20instils%20a%20rigorous%20(arguably%20pathological)%20work%20ethic%20in%20his%20sons%2C%20telling%20them%20that%20they%20can%20out-work%20this%20%E2%80%98curse%E2%80%99%20others%20seem%20to%20be%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20towering%20achievements%20of%20Durkin%E2%80%99s%20film%20is%20how%20it%20humanises%20the%20conservative%2C%20%E2%80%98red-state%E2%80%99%20family%20at%20its%20centre.%20Seeing%20them%20depicted%20as%20either%20cartoonishly%20upbeat%2C%20jolly%20good%20fellows%20or%20just%20outright%20evil%2C%20few%20mainstream%20films%20have%20tried%20to%20investigate%20the%20unnerving%20silences%20in%20this%20part%20of%20America.%20Like%20where%20the%20sons%20are%20instructed%20to%20take%20off%20their%20sunglasses%20at%20a%20brother%E2%80%99s%20funeral%2C%20and%20expressly%20told%20to%20not%20shed%20any%20tears.%20Or%20when%20the%20father%20wordlessly%20stares%20at%20the%20Democratic%20establishment%20boycotting%20the%201980%20Summer%20Olympics%20in%20USSR%20for%20their%20invasion%20of%20Afghanistan.%20There%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20moment%20when%20Kevin%20tries%20to%20speak%20with%20his%20mother%2C%20about%20their%20father%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20towards%20his%20youngest%20son%20Michael%20(Stanley%20Simons)%20because%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20show%20any%20inclination%20towards%20wrestling%2C%20and%20instead%20pursues%20his%20love%20for%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F8KVsaoveTbw%3Fsi%3DMMX57Zi0v_8GGcOl%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20in%20his%20earlier%20directorial%20features%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EMartha%20Marcy%20May%20Marlene%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Nest%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2020)%20%E2%80%93%20Durkin%E2%80%99s%20restraint%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Iron%20Claw%3C%2Fem%3E%20too%2C%20is%20masterful.%20In%20a%20scene%20right%20before%20a%20head-on%20collision%2C%20cinematographer%20Matyas%20Erdely%20places%20the%20camera%20near%20the%20front-wheel%20of%20a%20speeding%20motorbike%2C%20providing%20it%20with%20a%20visceral%2C%20foreboding%20energy.%20And%20then%20it%20cuts%20to%20black%2C%20with%20viewers%20finding%20out%20about%20the%20devastating%20consequences%20of%20the%20accident%20only%20in%20the%20next%20sequence.%20It%E2%80%99s%20this%20economy%20ensuring%20that%20Durkin%20is%20respectful%20of%20the%20tragedy%2C%20without%20mining%20it%20for%20tears%20and%2For%20hysteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDurkin%20assembles%20a%20terrific%20bunch%20of%20actors%20to%20play%20members%20of%20the%20Von%20Erich%20family.%20Zac%20Efron%20%E2%80%93%20a%20decade%20and%20a%20half%20since%20being%20a%20Disney%20heartthrob%20%E2%80%93%20is%20a%20revelation.%20Kevin%20is%20the%20audience%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20and%20ears%20as%20he%20goes%20from%20being%20the%20dutiful%20eldest%20son%20to%20a%20broken%2C%20haunted%20elder%20brother.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20tremendously%20physical%20performance%2C%20where%20Efron%20says%20more%20with%20his%20shrugs%20and%20nerves%2C%20as%20much%20as%20by%20throwing%20his%20body%20in%20the%20ring.%20Jeremy%20Allen%20White%2C%20who%20had%20his%20breakout%20moment%20in%202022%20series%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Bear%20%3C%2Fem%3E(co-incidentally%2C%20where%20he%E2%80%99s%20also%20playing%20a%20bereaved%20brother)%2C%20is%20searing%20as%20Kerry%2C%20singlemindedly%20trying%20to%20be%20the%20best%20son%20for%20his%20insatiable%20father%2C%20until%20he%20no%20longer%20can.%20A%20phone%20call%20between%20Kerry%20and%20Kevin%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20emotionally%20naked%20scenes%20I%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmongst%20all%20this%20testosterone%2C%20sweat%2C%20blood%20and%20muscle%20are%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20only%20two%20female%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20Doris%20and%20Kevin%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20Pam%20(Lily%20James).%20Lurking%20in%20the%20shadows%20for%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20134-minute%20runtime%2C%20both%20Doris%20and%20Pam%20get%20a%20couple%20of%20scenes%20where%20their%20agency%20is%20hinted%20at.%20However%2C%20the%20acting%20accolades%20belong%20to%20McCallany%20%E2%80%93%20playing%20the%20steely%2C%20unrepentant%20patriarch%20of%20the%20Von%20Erichs%20%E2%80%93%20where%20he%20%E2%80%98believes%E2%80%99%20in%20his%20mythology%20so%20fiercely%20that%20even%20the%20loss%20of%20a%20loved%20one%20does%20nothing%20to%20change%20him.%20What%20could%E2%80%99ve%20been%20a%20single-note%20monster%2C%20instead%20comes%20off%20as%20someone%20drunk%20on%20the%20ideals%20of%20American%20individualism.%20A%20case%20could%20be%20made%20for%20how%20Fritz%20Von%20Erich%20fancies%20himself%20as%20a%20glory-seeker%2C%20using%20his%20children%E2%80%99s%20bodies%20as%20fuel%20to%20make%20his%20place%20in%20the%20promised%20land%20of%20American%20wrestling.%20This%20reflects%20in%20Durkin%E2%80%99s%20choice%20to%20dwell%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20delusions%20driving%20them%20way%20beyond%20their%20breaking%20point%20and%20their%20children%E2%80%99s%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Iron%20Claw%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20cautionary%20tale%20for%20when%20families%20become%20cults%2C%20and%20patriarchs%20start%20acting%20like%20Gods.%20Its%20title%20is%20derived%20from%20a%20wrestling%20move%20adopted%20by%20Von%20Erich%20Sr.%2C%20which%20became%20a%20signature%20move%20for%20his%20sons%20too%2C%20where%20a%20wrestler%20gets%20hold%20of%20his%20opponents%E2%80%99%20temple%20and%20digs%20his%20fingers%20and%20nails%20into%20their%20skull%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20tap%20out%20of%20a%20fight.%20The%20title%20turns%20into%20a%20metaphor%20for%20Von%20Erich%E2%80%99s%20grip%20on%20his%20family%20and%20how%20they%20think.%20Durkin%20%E2%80%93%20whose%202011%20directorial%20debut%20followed%20the%20journey%20of%20a%20girl%20(a%20young%20Elizabeth%20Olsen)%20escaping%20the%20traumas%20of%20an%20abusive%20cult%20%E2%80%93%20is%20again%20patient%20and%20observant%20while%20piecing%20together%20a%20family%20portrait%20blown%20to%20pieces%20by%20generational%20values.%20The%20film%20seems%20to%20understand%20that%20being%20in%20a%20cult%20is%20like%20being%20held%20in%20a%20headlock%20by%20someone%20significantly%20stronger.%20Only%20some%20have%20enough%20clarity%20to%20tap%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707884105000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22htt