ion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inspectors%20concluded%20the%20site%20lacked%20a%20%26quot%3Bthorough%20safety%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20adequate%20communication%20of%20work%20rules%2C%20and%20a%20system%20to%20%26quot%3Bcorrect%20violations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20records%20said.%20The%20%26quot%3Bnear%20amputation%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20inspectors%20called%20it%2C%20occurred%20after%20a%20roll%20of%20material%20fell%20and%20crushed%20a%20worker's%20foot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManagers%20at%20SpaceX%20told%20the%20state%20inspectors%20that%20it%20was%20a%20one-time%20incident%20and%20the%20problem%20was%20fixed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInspectors%2C%20however%2C%20found%20that%20employees%20were%20not%20required%20to%20wear%20steel-toe%20shoes%2C%20even%20though%20the%20rolls%20of%20materials%20they%20had%20to%20load%20into%20a%20machine%20had%20gotten%20heavier%20-%20increasing%20from%20about%2080%20pounds%20to%20300%20pounds%20(36%20kg%20to%20136%20kg)%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20worker%20at%20the%20site%20told%20inspectors%20that%20%26quot%3Bsafety%20can%20get%20overlooked%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3Bgoal%20is%20to%20make%20as%20much%20as%20we%20can%20in%20a%20short%20amount%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20records.%20The%20injured%20worker%20said%20the%20machine%20where%20the%20rolls%20were%20loaded%20%26quot%3Bhad%20been%20deliberately%20set%20up%20incorrectly%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20increasing%20the%20production%20rate%20during%20the%20material%20loading%20phase.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20worker%2C%20who%20was%20not%20identified%20in%20the%20report%2C%20told%20inspectors%20that%20the%20matter%20had%20not%20been%20addressed%20and%20that%20safety%20officials%20at%20the%20company%20do%20not%20%26quot%3Bhave%20the%20reading%20comprehension%20nor%20the%20overall%20competency%20to%20implement%20a%20safety%20plan%20at%20the%20Redmond%20site.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20incident%20reported%20less%20t