atures%20upon%20Canada%20and%20the%20US.%3Cp%3ENOAA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20years%2C%20climate%20scientists%20thought%20that%20rising%20global%20temperatures%20would%20%3C%2Fspan%3Emake%20weather%20more%20erratic%20in%20every%20season%20except%20for%20winter%2C%20explained%20Judah%20Cohen%2C%20a%20climatologist%20at%20MIT.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsummer-2023-heat-wave-tracker-temperature-records-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erising%20global%20temperatures%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20should%20create%20milder%20winters%20with%20fewer%20storms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20in%20reality%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20climate%20change%20on%20winter%20weather%20is%20much%20more%20complex.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20another%20influence%20that%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20consider%20as%20recently%20as%20a%20decade%20ago%3A%20the%20way%20that%20climate%20change%20is%20occurring%20can%20influence%20the%20behavior%20of%20the%20polar%20vortex%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpolar-vortex-dangers-why-it-happens-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20polar%20vortex%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20large%20area%20of%20low%20pressure%20and%20cold%20air%20above%20the%20North%20and%20South%20Poles.%20It%E2%80%99s%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvortex%E2%80%9D%20because%20it%20flows%20counterclockwise%20in%20a%20continuous%20circle%20that%20keeps%20this%20cold%20air%20trapped%20at%20the%20poles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThink%20of%20it%20like%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprofessional-figure-skater-on-how-pain-altered-her-life-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efigure%20skater%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20said%20Cohen.%20To%20spin%20very%20fast%2C%20a%20figure%20skater%20has%20to%20tuck%20her%20arms%2C%20legs%2C%20and%20head%20into%20the%20center%20of%20her%20body.%20The%20same%20thing%20happens%20with%20the%20polar%20vortex.%20When%20it%20spins%20fast%2C%20the%20cold%20air%20stays%20tucked%20close%20to%20the%20center%20of%20rotation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20when%20the%20polar%20vortex%20slows%20down%2C%20its%20grip%20on%20this%20cold%20air%20loosens.%20This%20is%20what%20triggers%20Arctic%20outbreaks%20like%20Lorraine%3A%20when%20cold%20air%20in%20the%20polar%20jet%20stream%20surges%20down%20to%20lower%20latitudes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20loosening%20and%20tightening%20of%20this%20grip%20is%20normal.%20The%20polar%20vortex%20tends%20to%20weaken%20in%20the%20summer%20and%20strengthen%20in%20the%20winter.%20But%20climate%20change%20is%20disrupting%20this%20cycle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20way%20that%20climate%20change%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20Arctic%20is%20favoring%20this%20weak%20polar%20vortex%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20Cohen%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20when%20you%20get%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20probability%20of%20severe%20winter%20weather%2C%20cold%2C%20or%20snowfall.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWinter%20storm%20Lorraine%20is%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20this%20phenomenon.%20Last%20week%2C%20the%20polar%20vortex%20was%20strong%20and%20tight.%20But%20this%20week%2C%20it%20stretched%20out%20like%20a%20rubber%20band%2C%20Cohen%20said%2C%20sending%20a%20blast%20of%20cold%20temperatures%20and%20snowfall%20to%20the%20East%20Coast.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EArctic%20warming%20is%20disrupting%20the%20polar%20vortex%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Death%20Valley%20in%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a7bdf46075be0019c2eede%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDeath%20Valley%20in%20California%20last%20summer%20broke%20heat%20records.%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Williams-Ellis%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20David%20Becker%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClimate%20change%20is%20increasing%20global%20temperatures%20worldwide.%20But%20no%20place%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fun-report-devastating-arctic-temperature-rise-locked-in-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewarming%20faster%20than%20the%20Arctic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Research%20suggests%20that%20the%20North%20Pole%20has%20warmed%20two%20to%20four%20times%20faster%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20since%201990.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpolar-vortex-hitting-us-might-be-connected-to-global-warming-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erapid%20warming%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20likely%20what%E2%80%99s%20causing%20more%20frequent%20and%20extreme%20disruptions%20to%20the%20polar%20vortex%2C%20and%20unleashing%20the%20polar%20jet%20stream%20onto%20the%20mid-latitudes%2C%20Cohen%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20because%20rising%20Arctic%20temperatures%20have%20destabilized%20the%20way%20that%20air%20flows%20around%20the%20world.%20In%20particular%2C%20the%20warmer%20temperatures%20are%20amplifying%20a%20naturally%20occurring%20%E2%80%9Cwave%E2%80%9D%20of%20air%20that%20flows%20across%20Eurasia.%20When%20this%20amplified%20wave%20crashes%20into%20the%20polar%20vortex%2C%20it%20disrupts%20its%20circulation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20this%20happens%2C%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20face%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20wintry%20blast.%20%E2%80%9CNorth%20America%20is%20really%20ground%20zero%20for%20these%20types%20of%20events%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cohen%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20could%20explain%20why%20the%20US%20is%20still%20experiencing%20episodes%20of%20record-breaking%20low%20winter%20temperatures%20despite%20an%20overall%20rise%20in%20annual%20average%20temperatures%2C%20Cohen%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20year%202023%20may%20have%20been%20the%20hottest%20year%20on%20record%2C%20but%20some%20states%20still%20faced%20brutal%20cold.%20In%20February%20of%20that%20year%2C%20Boston%20recorded%20its%20coldest%20day%20since%201957%2C%20and%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%20saw%20its%20second%20snowiest%20day%20on%20record.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3EBrace%20for%20weirder%20winters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Snow%20covers%20the%20shore%20of%20Joe%20Pool%20Lake%20during%20a%20winter%20storm%20on%20January%2015%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ac5cd26979d73718252a8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESnow%20covers%20the%20shore%20of%20Joe%20Pool%20Lake%20during%20a%20winter%20storm%20in%20January.%3Cp%3EJulio%20Cortez%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhiplash%20weather%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20seem%20to%20be%20going%20away%20any%20time%20soon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20progression%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20the%20Arctic%20will%20continue%20to%20warm%2C%20and%20polar%20vortex%20disruptions%20could%20become%20increasingly%20common.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20promise%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20going%20to%20continue%20into%20the%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cohen%20said.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20a%20number%20of%20these%20events%20could%20continue%20as%20long%20as%20the%20conditions%20that%20support%20these%20disruptions%20continue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdapting%20to%20this