02%2F13163628%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.33.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x156.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163628%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.33.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x531.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696951%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22347%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Trading%20Economics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20see%20dramatic%20changes%20in%20the%20world%20economy%2C%20decoupling%20and%20rebalancing%2C%20the%20place%20to%20look%20is%20not%20to%20trade%2C%20but%20FDI%20(Foreign%20Direct%20Investment).%20Since%202022%2C%20inbound%20FDI%20to%20China%2C%20once%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20premier%20destination%2C%20has%20fallen%20off%20a%20cliff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20559px)%2085vw%2C%20559px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163616%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.34.07%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22559%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163616%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.34.07%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201106w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163616%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.34.07%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x277.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163616%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.34.07%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x944.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696950%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22516%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20interest%20rate%20hikes%20made%202022-2023%20a%20bad%20period%20for%20global%20capital%20flows%20generally.%20India%E2%80%99s%20FDI%20flows%20are%20off%20their%20peak%20too.%20But%20the%20Chinese%20collapse%20is%20dramatic%20and%20clearly%20reflects%20investor%20worries%20about%20geopolitics%20and%20the%20domestic%20policy%20regime%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20recently%20as%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20FDI%20to%20China%20was%20outstripping%20India%E2%80%99s%20by%20a%20huge%20margin.%20In%202023%20FDI%20to%20India%2C%20even%20running%20below%20its%20peak%20rate%20easily%20exceeded%20that.%20to%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20clearly%20does%20reflect%20a%20shift.%20But%20given%20the%20vast%20stock%20of%20foreign%20capital%20already%20committed%20to%20China%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20in%20the%20order%20of%20several%20trillions%20dollars%20%E2%80%93%20it%20will%20take%20years%20before%20the%20total%20foreign%20commitment%20to%20India%20will%20match%20that%20already%20committed%20to%20China.%20The%20huge%20investments%20by%20Apple%20and%20Tesla%20are%20indicative%20both%20of%20the%20change%20in%20direction%20and%20the%20time%20and%20money%20it%20will%20take%20to%20achieve%20a%20substantial%20rebalancing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20given%20China%E2%80%99s%20sophistication%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20the%20political%20pressures%20for%20decoupling%2C%20one%20would%20in%20any%20case%20expect%20a%20rebalancing%20from%20foreign-led%20investment%20into%20China%2C%20to%20Chinese-led%20investment%20in%20locations%20like%20Vietnam%2C%20Mexico%20etc.%20As%20China%20develops%2C%20it%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20the%20net%20balance%20of%20direct%20investment%20should%20shift%20from%20a%20large%20surplus%20to%20a%20deficit.%20Added%20to%20which%2C%20given%20China%E2%80%99s%20vast%20current%20account%20surplus%2C%20we%20would%20expect%20the%20capital%20account%20to%20be%20in%20deficit%20i.e.%20for%20China%20to%20be%20exporting%20rather%20than%20importing%20capital.%20China%20cannot%20import%20capital%20on%20a%20huge%20scale%20whilst%20exporting%20the%20way%20it%20does.%20The%20giant%20infrastructure%20projects%20of%20One%20Belt%20One%20Road%20were%20once%20widely%20seen%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cescape%20valve%E2%80%9D%20for%20China%E2%80%99s%20surpluses.%20That%20was%20Chinese%20out-bound%20FDI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20unusual%20and%20important%20aspects%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20globalization%20is%20that%20it%20was%20led%20by%20trade%20and%20FDI%20i.e.%20international%20flows%20directly%20connected%20to%20the%20production%20and%20distribution%20of%20goods.%20By%20contrast%2C%20portfolio%20investment%2C%20the%20variable%20that%20the%20Bloomberg%20article%20focuses%20on%2C%20the%20acquisition%20across%20borders%20of%20financial%20claims%20in%20the%20form%20of%20bonds%20and%20equities%2C%20has%20only%20recently%20taken%20on%20any%20significance%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163604%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.34.13%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22678%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163604%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.34.13%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201068w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163604%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.34.13%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x214.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F13163604%2FScreenshot-2024-02-13-at-4.34.13%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x731.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696949%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22484%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20striking%20feature%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20international%20balance%20sheet%20that%20on%20the%20liability%20side%20(i.e%20foreign%20claims)%20inward%20FDI%20is%20more%20than%20two%20times%20larger%20than%20foreign%20portfolio%20claims.%20Meanwhile%20on%20the%20Chinese%20asset%20side%2C%20private%20portfolio%20claims%20are%20a%20very%20minor%20component%2C%20dwarfed%20by%20Chinese%20FDI%20and%20even%20more%20by%20official%20reserves%20and%20quasi-official%20reserves%20(other)%20held%20on%20the%20balance%20sheets%20of%20state%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20look%20at%20US%20Treasury%20data%20on%20US%20holdings%20of%20foreign%20financial%20assets%20it%20would%20seem%20that%20US%20investor%20claims%20against%20India%20already%20exceed%20those%20against%20China%20%E2%80%93%20%24287%20billion%20to%20%24243%20billion.%20If%20anyone%20took%20those%20numbers%20at%20face%20value%20there%20would%20be%20no%20cause%20to%20write%20the%20kind%20of%20piece%20that%20appeared%20in%20Bloomberg.%20The%20numbers%20are%20misleading%20because%20they%20fail%20to%20capture%20all%20the%20indirect%20ways%20in%20which%20US%20investors%2C%20notably%20those%20of%20the%20hedge%20fund%20variety%2C%20actually%20locate%20their%20holdings%20of%20financial%20assets.%20Much%20of%20it%20is%20held%20offshore%20or%20through%20indirect%20vehicles%2C%20not%20captured%20in%20the%20Treasury%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F5f8e6e41-6d2f-46eb-a90c-cce958f067e6%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiMWc3ZDkifQ.ANHu2vRAyuFpjv7uiZBbU4uAYv19NWdGMb8wTAqqIz8%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F5f8e6e41-6d2f-46eb-a90c-cce958f067e6%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiMWc3ZDkifQ.ANHu2vRAyuFpjv7uiZBbU4uAYv19NWdGMb8wTAqqIz8%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1707907956072000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3SBXdGM8jSVATL8H6YAxKs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERhodium%20group%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0prepared%20an%20in-depth%20report%20on%20the%20depth%20of%20US%20China%20financial%20connections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%