ree%20Movement%20With%20Myanmar%20Raises%20Concerns%20in%20Nagaland%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F22133126%2FScreenshot-2024-01-22-at-1.27.44.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20recent%20decision%20to%20end%20the%20free%20movement%20regime%20(FMR)%20with%20Myanmar%20has%20rattled%20civil%20society%20in%20Nagaland%20%E2%80%93%20so%20much%20so%20that%20a%20powerful%20students%E2%80%99%20body%2C%20the%20Naga%20Students%20Federation%20(NSF)%2C%20has%20shot%20off%20an%20appeal%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20seeking%20its%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%20intervention%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20Dimapur%2C%20NSF%20president%20Medovi%20Rhi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20arbitrary%20intervention%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20will%20certainly%20affect%20the%20ongoing%20Naga%20peace%20talks%20as%20the%20Central%20government%20also%20needs%20to%20be%20equally%20sincere%20and%20committed%20to%20bring%20peace.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedovi%20said%20India%E2%80%99s%20termination%20of%20the%20FMR%20understanding%20with%20Myanmar%20as%20per%20which%20people%20of%20the%20border%20areas%20on%20either%20side%20are%20allowed%20free%20movement%20till%20a%2016%20km%20radius%20will%20%E2%80%9Conce%20more%20divide%20the%20Naga%20people%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20abolish%20the%20FMR%20arrangement%20with%20Myanmar%20comes%20soon%20after%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%E2%80%99s%20announcement%20on%20February%206%20on%20fencing%20the%20entire%20border%20with%20Myanmar.%20The%201%2C643-km-long%20border%20of%20India%20with%20Myanmar%20is%20along%20the%20north-eastern%20states%20of%20Nagaland%2C%20Mizoram%2C%20Manipur%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20when%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20remove%20the%20FMR%20agreement%20along%20Nagaland%E2%80%99s%20215-km%20border%20with%20Myanmar%20reached%20the%20state%2C%20widespread%20civil%20society%20opposition%20came%20to%20the%20surface.%20Representative%20bodies%20of%20several%20Naga%20tribes%20including%20the%20Eastern%20Nagaland%20People%E2%80%99s%20Organisation%20(ENPO)%20expressed%20their%20views%20differing%20with%20the%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20decision.%20It%20was%20the%20top%20news%20in%20all%20local%20newspapers%20on%20February%209%2C%20including%20the%20NSF%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20to%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20addressed%20to%20UN%20secretary%20general%20Antonio%20Guterres%20by%20NSF%20president%20Medovi%20Rhi%20was%20also%20published%20in%20full%20in%20the%20local%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3ENagaland%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20delineating%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20unique%20history%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Naga%20people%2C%20NSF%20accused%20the%20governments%20of%20Myanmar%20and%20India%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdividing%E2%80%9D%20the%20Naga%20homeland%20into%20two%20countries.%20It%20called%20India%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20end%20the%20FMR%20understanding%20with%20Myanmar%20%E2%80%9Ca%20ploy%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ca%20clear%20evidence%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20insincerity%20and%20insensitivity%20towards%20the%20inherent%20Naga%20birth%20right%20and%20the%20hope%20of%20the%20Naga%20people%20to%20once%20again%20live%20as%20free%20people%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReminding%20the%20UN%20about%20conducting%20%E2%80%9Ca%20plebiscite%20on%20May%2016%2C%201951%20wherein%2099.9%20per%20cent%20(of%20Nagas)%20wanted%20Independence%20from%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%20NSF%E2%80%99s%20letter%20to%20the%20UN%20secretary%20general%20urged%20not%20only%20the%20international%20body%20but%20the%20government%20of%20India%20to%20also%20%E2%80%9Cexplore%20the%20possibilities%20for%20a%20fresh%20referendum%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20international%20bodies%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedovi%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20imaginary%20line%20drawn%20between%20Myanmar%20and%20India%20is%20anyway%20absolutely%20arbitrary%20and%20made%20without%20keeping%20our%20history%20in%20mind.%20That%20in%20some%20villages%2C%20the%20international%20border%20runs%20through%20some%20people%E2%80%99s%20houses%20proves%20my%20point.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20Longwa%20village%20in%20Mon%20district%2C%20the%20international%20border%20runs%20through%20the%20chief%E2%80%99s%20house%2C%20dividing%20his%20living%20quarters%20and%20the%20kitchen.%20I%20want%20to%20ask%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20how%20are%20we%20to%20implement%20termination%20of%20FMR%20in%20those%20areas%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20being%20asked%20if%20NSF%20has%20received%20any%20response%20form%20the%20UN%2C%20Medovi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20emailed%20the%20letter%20to%20his%20office%20but%20the%20physical%20letter%20is%20still%20being%20readied%20which%20should%20go%20out%20soon.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20all%20top%20tribal%20Hohos%20of%20Nagaland%20have%20urged%20the%20Nagaland%20government%20to%20intervene%2C%20leading%20the%20Neiphiu%20Rio%20cabinet%20to%20take%20a%20resolution%20to%20appeal%20to%20the%20Centre%20to%20continue%20the%20FMR%20arrangement.%20Rio%20had%20earlier%20acknowledged%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20concerns%20considering%20the%20ongoing%20civil%20war%20in%20Myanmar%20but%20stated%20that%20the%20FRM%20needs%20to%20be%20regulated%20and%20not%20abolished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20the%20Nagaland%20assembly%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fcentre-asked-to-urge-myanmar-to-drop-border-fencing-project%2Farticleshow%2F57871361.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Etaken%20a%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20urge%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20to%20intervene%20when%20the%20Myanmar%20government%20had%20announced%20its%20fencing%20exercise%20along%20that%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20news%20reports%2C%20the%20Rio%20government%20is%20also%20set%20to%20discuss%20the%20matter%20with%20the%20civil%20society%20groups%20and%20leaders%20of%20various%20Naga%20tribes%20on%20how%20to%20proceed%20further%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Union%20minister%20had%20announced%20the%20decision%20to%20fence%20the%20border%2C%20Manipur%20chief%20minister%20N.%20Biren%20Singh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fcentre-set-to-take-key-decisions-related-to-manipur-cm-101706988341947.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20told%20reporters%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20Delhi%20that%20the%20Centre%20had%20decided%20to%20take%20%E2%80%9Ckey%20decisions%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20Manipur%20issue.%20Biren%20had%20made%20that%20announcement%20after%20a%20meeting%20with%20Amit%20Shah%20on%20February%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%206%2C%20Shah%20announced%20his%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Findia-to-fence-entire-border-with-myanmar%2Farticle67818240.ece%5C%22%3Efence%20the%20border%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20longstanding%20demand%20of%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20majority%20Meitei%20community.%20The%20demand%20of%20the%20community%20to%20fence%20the%20Myanmar%20border%20came%20to%20the%20fore%20once%20again%20after%20the%20ethnic%20fight%20broke%20out%20with%20the%20Kukis%20of%20Manipur.%20Like%20the%20Nagas%20and%20the%20Mizos%2C%20Kukis%20of%20Manipur%20also%20share%20kinship%20with%20people%20residing%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20international%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20with%20the%20same%20concern%20that%20Mizoram%E2%80%99s%20lone%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20K.%20Vanlalvena%20had%20urged%20Shah%20this%20February%2010%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatvnews.com%2Fmizoram%2Fmizoram-mp-k-vanlalvena-urges-amit-shah-to-reconsider-decision-to-fence-india-myanmar-border-latest-updates-2024-02-10-9162